  "body": "### Problem:\r\nAfter performing a long tap on a specific reaction in a message, the user is navigated to a different reaction in the 'who sent' screen instead of the intended reaction.\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce:\r\n1. Open any chat.\r\n2. Leave a reaction on a message.\r\n3. Long tap the reaction \r\n4. Check which reaction is shown as selected in the 'who sent' page.\r\n\r\n### Actual Behavior:\r\nThe long-tapped reaction is not visually marked as selected in the 'who sent' page\r\n\r\n(see on record. \r\n- In sec 3 the  üëé is long tapped, but the  üëç is selected instead. \r\n- On 26 second üòÑ is long tapped, but   üëé is selected instead)\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/assets/52490791/8d6150fa-bd1e-4349-be32-a71661ca3967\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Expected Behavior:\r\nThe long-tapped reaction should be visually marked as selected in the 'who sent' page.\r\n\r\n### Additional info:\r\nReproduced in 10% of cases. Try randomly long tap a few reactions to reproduce\r\n\r\n### ENV:\r\n- Nightly 5 Jun 2023",
